('aberdour', 'Aberdour', 'https://www.brsgolf.com/aberdour/visitor_home.php', 'https://www.brsgolf.com/aberdour/visitor_home.php', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'brs', 'brs', '', 'fife', 'Yes', 56.047091, -3.306216, 0, 0, '', '', '', 0, 'aberdour', 1, 0, 'd', 0xe610000001010000007218cc5f21730ac0cd77f01307064c40, 'nonlinks', 'No', 'Aberdour Golf Club is a charming parkland course located on the southern shores of the Firth of Forth in Fife. Established in the late 19th century, it combines traditional Scottish golf design with the beauty of its coastal surroundings. The course features gently undulating fairways lined with mature trees, strategic bunkering, and greens that demand accuracy and careful approach shots.\r\n\r\nWhile not overly long, Aberdour provides a subtle challenge, particularly when coastal winds influence club selection and strategy.\r\n\r\nSeveral holes offer scenic views of the Firth of Forth, adding a serene maritime atmosphere that enhances the overall experience. The layout balances accessibility for beginners with a rewarding test for more experienced golfers, making it versatile for all skill levels. Off the course, the welcoming, community-focused club atmosphere ensures that visitors feel immediately at home.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nAberdour Golf Club has earned a reputation as a hidden gem on Fife\'s golfing map, offering a peaceful round in a picturesque coastal setting. Its combination of natural beauty, thoughtful design, and friendly hospitality makes it an ideal choice for golfers seeking a traditional Scottish experience away from the crowds of larger, more commercial venues.', ''),
('Aberfeldy', 'Aberfeldy', 'https://www.aberfeldy-golfclub.co.uk/', '', 'No', 'No', '', '', '', 'highlands', '', 56.621756, -3.871285, 0, 0, '', '', '', 0, '', 0, 0, 'd', 0xe61000000101000000bf0b5bb3954f4c407ff6234564f80ec0, 'nonlinks', 'No', 'Aberfeldy Golf Club is a charming, traditional Scottish golf course nestled in the scenic town of Aberfeldy, in the heart of Perthshire. Established in the early 20th century, the course combines parkland and moorland features, offering a blend of strategy and natural beauty that appeals to golfers of all abilities. Rolling fairways wind through mature trees, with subtle elevation changes providing both challenge and variety throughout the round.\r\n\r\nThe layout emphasizes precision over power, rewarding thoughtful shot placement and careful navigation of bunkers and natural hazards. Several holes feature views of the surrounding Highland hills and the nearby River Tay, creating a tranquil backdrop that enhances the golfing experience. The greens are well-maintained and subtly contoured, demanding a careful and confident putting stroke.\r\n\r\nAberfeldy Golf Club is known for its warm, welcoming atmosphere, reflecting the friendly spirit of the local community. While modest in length, the course\'s design challenges players with strategic choices and the occasional Highland breeze that can alter play. For visitors, it offers an authentic Scottish golfing experience, combining history, natural beauty, and enjoyable playability. Aberfeldy is a must-visit for anyone looking to enjoy a classic, scenic course away from the crowds of Scotland\'s more famous links.', ''),
('aberfoyle', 'Aberfoyle', 'https://www.aberfoylegolf.co.uk/visitors', 'https://www.aberfoylegolf.co.uk/visitors', 'No', 'No', '', '', '', 'central', '', 56.175030, -4.362100, 0, 0, '', '', '', 0, '', 0, 0, 'd', 0xe61000000101000000c286a757ca7211c0d1e80e6267164c40, 'nonlinks', 'No', 'Aberfoyle Golf Club is located in the heart of the Trossachs, surrounded by lush woodlands, rolling hills, and tranquil scenery. This parkland course provides a picturesque and immersive golfing experience, combining natural beauty with strategic design. Tree-lined fairways, subtle elevation changes, and well-positioned bunkers create a layout that rewards accurate drives and thoughtful approach shots.\r\n\r\nThe undulating terrain and elevated greens require careful planning and precise putting, while the surrounding landscape enhances a sense of seclusion and relaxation. The course is approachable for golfers of all skill levels, offering a welcoming environment that balances accessibility with challenge.\r\n\r\nThe club\'s friendly, community-driven atmosphere ensures that visitors feel at home, and its scenic setting encourages golfers to take in the natural beauty of central Scotland while enjoying their round. Aberfoyle Golf Club delivers a classic Highland experience, blending strategic shot-making with breathtaking scenery. Its combination of woodland beauty, thoughtful design, and peaceful surroundings makes it a memorable destination for those exploring the Trossachs region.', ''),
('abernethy', 'Abernethy', 'https://www.abernethygolfclub.com/Teebooking/SearchSlots.aspx', 'https://www.abernethygolfclub.com/Teebooking/SearchSlots.aspx', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'dotgolf', 'scottishgolf', '', 'highlands', 'Yes', 57.269830, -3.653280, 0, 2009, '', '', '', 0, '', 0, 0, 'd', 0xe6100000010100000066bd18ca89a24c400b0c59ddea390dc0, 'nonlinks', 'No', 'Abernethy Golf Club, located in the Scottish Highlands, is a serene and challenging course that blends parkland and natural landscapes. The layout features mature trees, gently rolling fairways, and subtle bunkering, encouraging golfers to focus on strategic shot-making rather than raw power. Its modest length belies the challenge, as careful placement and consideration of the land\'s natural contours are essential for scoring well.\r\n\r\nSurrounded by the dramatic scenery of the Highlands, the course offers a peaceful retreat, with panoramic views of distant hills and forests. The club is highly regarded for its welcoming and community-oriented atmosphere, providing a friendly environment for visitors while maintaining the strategic challenges that experienced golfers appreciate.\r\n\r\nAbernethy is a true hidden gem of Highland golf, offering both relaxation and a competitive test. Its combination of natural beauty, thoughtful design, and tranquil surroundings makes it ideal for golfers seeking an authentic Scottish golfing experience away from more commercialized courses. Every round is memorable, with the serene environment enhancing both enjoyment and focus.', ''),
('aboyne', 'Aboyne', 'https://visitors.brsgolf.com/aboyne#/course/1', 'https://visitors.brsgolf.com/aboyne#/course/1', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'brs', 'brs', '', 'aberdeen', 'Yes', 57.083963, -2.770209, 0, 0, '', '', '', 0, 'aboyne', 1, 0, 'd', 0xe61000000101000000cdad1056632906c07a89b14cbf8a4c40, 'nonlinks', 'No', 'Aboyne Golf Club is situated on the edge of Royal Deeside, offering a classic parkland layout with a mix of challenge and scenic beauty. Rolling fairways are lined with mature trees, while well-maintained greens demand precision on approaches. The course takes full advantage of the gentle Highland terrain, providing a layout that rewards strategic play and careful shot selection.\r\n\r\nSeveral holes offer sweeping views of the surrounding hills and valleys, giving golfers a sense of openness and connection to the landscape. Aboyne balances accessibility with subtle difficulty, making it enjoyable for beginners while still offering a thoughtful test for more experienced players.\r\n\r\nThe club is renowned for its welcoming and friendly atmosphere, reflecting the strong community spirit of Aberdeenshire. Golfers visiting Aboyne can enjoy both the strategic challenge of the course and the relaxed environment, making it an ideal venue for casual rounds or more focused play. With its combination of scenic Highland vistas, thoughtful course design, and warm hospitality, Aboyne Golf Club provides a memorable and authentic Scottish golfing experience.', ''),
