('ailsa', 'Turnberry - Ailsa', 'https://www.turnberry.co.uk/', '', 'Yes', 'No', 'turnberry', '', '', 'ayrshire', '', 55.315405, -4.833056, 24432, 0, '', '', '', 0, '', 0, 1, 'a', 0xe6100000010100000041f2cea10c5513c058ffe7305fa84b40, 'links', 'Yes', 'Turnberry\'s Ailsa Course is one of the world\'s most iconic links courses, perched dramatically along the Ayrshire coastline. Opened in 1906, the course has hosted multiple Open Championships and offers a historic yet modern golfing experience. Its undulating fairways are framed by coastal dunes and cliffs, with strategic bunkering and large, contoured greens demanding precision and thoughtful play.\r\n\r\nThe Ailsa Course is famed for its breathtaking scenery, including views of the Isle of Arran, the Mull of Kintyre, and the iconic Turnberry Lighthouse. Firm fairways and windswept conditions make club selection and shot execution crucial, providing a challenging test for all skill levels. The par-70 layout emphasizes strategy over power, rewarding careful planning and creative shot-making.\r\n\r\nBeyond its competitive prestige, Turnberry offers a luxurious and welcoming environment, with a rich history and world-class facilities that enhance the golfing experience. Whether tackling championship-level holes or simply enjoying the dramatic seaside vistas, golfers at the Ailsa Course experience the perfect combination of heritage, challenge, and natural beauty, making it a must-play destination in Scotland.', ''),
