('Dalbeattie', 'Dalbeattie', 'https://www.dalbeattiegolfclub.co.uk/', '', 'No', 'No', '', '', '', 'south', '', 54.938879, -3.829159, 0, 0, '', '', '', 0, '', 0, 0, 'd', 0xe61000000101000000f778211d1ea20ec05af3e32f2d784b40, 'nonlinks', 'No', 'Dalbeattie Golf Club, in Dumfries & Galloway, is a scenic parkland course established in 1898. Measuring approximately 6,100 yards with a par of 70, it features tree-lined fairways, water hazards, and subtly contoured greens.\r\n\r\nNotable holes include the par-3 5th over a pond and the par-4 12th, with strategic bunkering and elevation changes. While Dalbeattie has not hosted major professional events, it is a central hub for local amateur competitions and society golf.\r\n\r\nThe clubhouse overlooks key holes, providing a welcoming social space. Its natural beauty, historic roots, and community atmosphere make Dalbeattie a quintessential southwest Scottish parkland course.', ''),
('Dalfaber', 'Dalfaber', '', '', 'No', 'No', '', '', '', 'highlands', '', 57.199305, -3.809645, 0, 0, '', '', '', 0, '', 0, 0, 'd', 0xe6100000010100000099f56228277a0ec0f37684d382994c40, 'nonlinks', 'No', 'Dalfaber Golf Club, located near Aviemore, is a modern championship-style parkland course set amidst the stunning Cairngorms landscape. Opened in 1989, it was designed to blend seamlessly into the surrounding Highland scenery, taking full advantage of gentle slopes, mature trees, and natural water features. The full 18 holes measure around 6,400 yards with a par of 72.\r\n\r\nThe course is notable for its strategic variety: tight tree-lined fairways demand accurate driving, while elevated greens and subtle bunkering test approach play. The par-5 7th and par-4 16th are standout holes, challenging golfers to balance risk and reward.\r\n\r\nDalfaber has become a favourite for both members and visitors, attracting society days and regional competitions, though it has not hosted major professional events. Its proximity to the Cairngorms National Park makes it ideal for golfers seeking scenic surroundings alongside quality play.\r\n\r\nThe clubhouse provides panoramic views of the Highlands, with hospitality that complements the natural beauty of the course. Dalfaber embodies the modern Highland parkland style: strategic, picturesque, and welcoming for all levels.', ''),
('dalmahoy', 'Dalmahoy - East', 'https://visitors.brsgolf.com/dalmahoy#/course/1', 'https://visitors.brsgolf.com/dalmahoy#/course/1', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'brs', 'brs', '', 'edinburgh', 'Yes', 55.901576, -3.363634, 0, 0, '', '', '', 0, 'dalmahoy', 1, 0, 'd', 0xe6100000010100000095b54df1b8e80ac0e36da5d766f34b40, 'nonlinks', 'No', 'Dalmahoy East, near Edinburgh, is part of the prestigious Dalmahoy Estate, a renowned golfing destination. Originally designed by James Braid in the early 20th century, the East Course has been reworked over the years but retains its classic parkland character. It measures around 6,700 yards with a par of 72.\r\n\r\nThe course blends tree-lined fairways, rolling terrain, and strategic bunkering. Notable holes include the par-4 14th, requiring a well-placed drive to navigate a sweeping dogleg, and the par-3 11th, elevated with a protected green. Dalmahoy East has hosted amateur and corporate competitions, maintaining a reputation for quality and challenge near the capital.\r\n\r\nThe estate\'s clubhouse provides top-class amenities, dining, and event facilities, making Dalmahoy East not just a golf venue but a social and cultural hub. Its long history, strategic layout, and scenic appeal make it one of the standout parkland tests in Scotland.', ''),
